<TITLE> Arms, ammo seized in Chittagong, Sylhet </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, July 3 (bdnews24.com)  The police seized a sizeable cache of arms and ammunition early Tuesday from the rubber plantation area of Kanchan Nagar in Fatikchhari upazila. In Sylhet, RAB in a swoop arrested a notorious pro-Awami League student activist and retrieved arms and ammunition from him, officials said. Fatikchhari Police Station duty officer sub-inspector Enamul Haque told bdnews24.com that tipped off, a police contingent led by officer in charge MA Jalil raided the rubber plantation area at around 1:30am and retrieved the cache of arms and ammunition. The cache in Fatikchhari included a G-3 rifle and three magazines, one 303 rifle and a magazine, one .22 bore air-gun and 245 rounds of 303 rifle bullets, 75 rounds of G-3 bullets and 24 rounds of M-16 rifle bullets. The elite crime busters raided the home of Bidhan Kumar Saha and arrested him early Tuesday, Rab-9 officer Lt Colonel Ferdous Khan said. They later seized two US-made shotguns, one AK-22, two magazines and one revolver from him. Bidhan, a former organising secretary of Bangladesh Chhatra League, is allegedly involved in illegal arms business, Khan said. Another Rab official, who would not be named, said there were several charges including for murder and attacks on the police against Bidhan. The Rab officials said they would turn him over to the police after initial interrogation. bdnews24.com/ff/ra/
